{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849378177,"sessionID":"ses_287215b25ffe7CZXXnfStOQX5W","part":{"id":"prt_d78df0cfc001ZvhmYbsoBp9f62","messageID":"msg_d78def922001DIoPUf4QXLjT3N","sessionID":"ses_287215b25ffe7CZXXnfStOQX5W","type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"toolu_fa46fab8b0864ad095580410","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z","pattern":"jwt|JWT"},"output":"Found 179 matches (showing first 100)\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/.sdd_prompt.md:\n  Line 3: AR: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md:\n  Line 1: # Proposal: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n  Line 5: Implement JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication and token issuance capabilities in `pkg/router` to replace the current static bearer token authentication. This enables stateless authentication, token expiration, claims-based authorization, and integration with external identity providers.\n  Line 30: Implement JWT-based authentication that:\n  Line 31: - Validates JWT tokens using cryptographic signatures (HMAC or RSA)\n  Line 55: | JWT Validator | Validate JWT signatures, expiration, issuer, audience |\n  Line 57: | Token Issuer | Issue JWT tokens on successful authentication |\n  Line 59: | Middleware Integration | Replace existing auth middleware with JWT validation |\n  Line 60: | Configuration | JWT secret, algorithms, expiration, issuer settings |\n  Line 67: ├── jwt/\n  Line 68: │   ├── validator.go          # JWT validation logic\n  Line 72: │   └── config.go             # JWT configuration\n  Line 73: ├── auth.go                   # Update to use JWT (existing)\n  Line 79: The router supports these new JWT configuration options:\n  Line 83: | JWTEnabled | bool | false | Enable JWT authentication |\n  Line 84: | JWTSecretKey | string | \"\" | Secret key for HS256 signing |\n  Line 85: | JWTPublicKeyFile | string | \"\" | Public key file for RS256 |\n  Line 86: | JWTPrivateKeyFile | string | \"\" | Private key file for RS256 |\n  Line 87: | JWTAlgorithm | string | \"HS256 | Signing algorithm (HS256, RS256, ES256) |\n  Line 88: | JWTIssuer | string | \"agentcube\" | Token issuer claim |\n  Line 89: | JWTAudience | []string | [] | Expected audience claims |\n  Line 90: | JWTAccessTokenTTL | duration | 15m | Access token time-to-live |\n  Line 91: | JWTRefreshTokenTTL | duration | 24h | Refresh token time-to-live |\n  Line 92: | JWTIssuerEndpoint | string | \"/auth/token\" | Token issuance endpoint |\n  Line 93: | JWTValidateOnStart | bool | true | Validate keys on startup |\n  Line 97: - Distributed JWT validation (shared keys) — future enhancement\n  Line 99: - Multi-tenant JWT claims — future enhancement\n  Line 109: | github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5 | ^5.2 | JWT parsing and validation |\n  Line 115: - **AR-010 Session Management** — JWT tokens integrate with session store\n  Line 120: 1. **External Clients** — Obtain and use JWT tokens for API access\n  Line 121: 2. **Backend Services** — Validate JWT claims from router\n  Line 122: 3. **Monitoring Systems** — JWT metrics for security auditing\n  Line 138: ### Option 1: JWT with Symmetric Keys (HS256) (Selected)\n  Line 140: **Approach**: Use a shared secret key for signing and validating JWT tokens.\n  Line 156: ### Option 2: JWT with Asymmetric Keys (RS256)\n  Line 196: **Approach**: Use PASETO instead of JWT.\n  Line 208: **Decision**: Rejected — JWT has broader ecosystem support and sufficient security for current use cases.\n  Line 214: ### Phase 1: JWT Core\n  Line 215: - [ ] Define JWT configuration struct\n  Line 218: - [ ] Implement JWT validator with signature verification\n  Line 229: - [ ] Update Authenticator to use JWT validator\n  Line 235: - [ ] Link JWT claims with session management (AR-010)\n  Line 236: - [ ] Store user ID from JWT in session\n  Line 237: - [ ] Enable session creation on JWT validation\n  Line 241: - [ ] Track JWT validation attempts (success/failure)\n  Line 244: - [ ] Add JWT-specific error logging\n  Line 247: - [ ] Unit tests for JWT validation\n  Line 257: - [ ] JWT tokens are validated using configured algorithm\n  Line 263: - [ ] JWT middleware integrates with existing auth infrastructure\n  Line 265: - [ ] JWT metrics are exported (jwt_validated_total, jwt_issued_total, jwt_validation_errors_total)\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md:\n  Line 1: # Delta Spec: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n  Line 5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing JWT authentication and token issuance in `pkg/router`.\n  Line 18: The router module requires JWT-based authentication to secure API endpoints and enable token-based access control. This includes both JWT validation for incoming requests and token issuance for authenticated clients.\n  Line 22: ## Requirement: JWT Configuration\n  Line 24: ### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with default configuration\n  Line 26: **GIVEN** a Router instance is created with `jwtEnabled: true` and no explicit JWT configuration\n  Line 30: ### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with custom configuration\n  Line 32: **GIVEN** a Router instance with JWT configuration: `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"`, `jwtExpiry: \"24h\"`, `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n  Line 36: ### Scenario: Router disables JWT authentication\n  Line 38: **GIVEN** a Router instance with `jwtEnabled: false` (default)\n  Line 40: **THEN** the router SHOULD NOT validate JWT tokens\n  Line 41: **AND** no JWT middleware SHOULD be applied\n  Line 45: ## Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n  Line 47: ### Scenario: Router validates valid JWT token\n  Line 49: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and configured secret\n  Line 50: **WHEN** a request arrives with a valid JWT token in Authorization header \"Bearer <valid-token>\"\n  Line 54: ### Scenario: Router rejects expired JWT token\n  Line 56: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n  Line 57: **WHEN** a request arrives with an expired JWT token\n  Line 61: ### Scenario: Router rejects invalid signature JWT token\n  Line 63: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n  Line 64: **WHEN** a request arrives with a JWT token that has invalid signature\n  Line 68: ### Scenario: Router rejects malformed JWT token\n  Line 70: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n  Line 71: **WHEN** a request arrives with a malformed JWT token (not 3 parts)\n  Line 75: ### Scenario: Router extracts claims from valid JWT\n  Line 77: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n  Line 78: **WHEN** a request arrives with valid JWT containing claims: `sub`, `exp`, `roles`\n  Line 84: ## Requirement: JWT Token Issuance\n  Line 86: ### Scenario: Router issues JWT token for valid credentials\n  Line 88: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint configured\n  Line 91: **AND** issue a JWT token with user claims\n  Line 94: ### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured expiry\n  Line 96: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtExpiry: \"2h\"`\n  Line 100: ### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured issuer\n  Line 102: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n  Line 108: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint\n  Line 111: **AND** NOT issue a JWT token\n  Line 115: ## Requirement: JWT Middleware\n  Line 117: ### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from Authorization header\n  Line 119: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n  Line 124: ### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from query parameter\n  Line 126: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware configured to allow query param\n  Line 131: ### Scenario: JWT middleware allows public endpoints\n  Line 133: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n  Line 135: **THEN** the middleware SHOULD skip JWT validation\n  Line 138: ### Scenario: JWT middleware blocks unauthorized access\n  Line 140: **GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n  Line 146: ## Requirement: JWT Claims\n  Line 148: ### Scenario: Router includes user ID in JWT claims\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 179 matches (79 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":179,"truncated":true},"title":"jwt|JWT","time":{"start":1775849378166,"end":1775849378174}}}}
