{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775849394627,"sessionID":"ses_287215b25ffe7CZXXnfStOQX5W","part":{"id":"prt_d78df51bf001cwUbwNCi57nEA1","messageID":"msg_d78df43f4001cF7Aqaionkc7ui","sessionID":"ses_287215b25ffe7CZXXnfStOQX5W","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775849404132,"sessionID":"ses_287215b25ffe7CZXXnfStOQX5W","part":{"id":"prt_d78df73ec001uwH58tOi6JNArS","messageID":"msg_d78df43f4001cF7Aqaionkc7ui","sessionID":"ses_287215b25ffe7CZXXnfStOQX5W","type":"text","text":"The delta-spec.md already exists and is comprehensive. Let me enhance it with additional scenarios from the proposal that are missing (metrics, audience validation, clock skew):","time":{"start":1775849404130,"end":1775849404130}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775849418085,"sessionID":"ses_287215b25ffe7CZXXnfStOQX5W","part":{"id":"prt_d78df76e4001a5yZRKd2c68es4","messageID":"msg_d78df43f4001cF7Aqaionkc7ui","sessionID":"ses_287215b25ffe7CZXXnfStOQX5W","type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"toolu_42bf418058ba403681ee8d5e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","newString":"## Requirement: Key Management\n\n### Scenario: Router loads JWT secret from configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtSecret: \"my-secret-key\"` configured\n**WHEN** JWT validation or issuance occurs\n**THEN** the router SHOULD use \"my-secret-key\" for signing/verification\n\n### Scenario: Router supports RS256 with private key\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and private key configured\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD be signed with RS256 using the private key\n\n### Scenario: Router validates RS256 token with public key\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and public key configured\n**WHEN** a request arrives with RS256-signed JWT\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate using the public key\n\n### Scenario: Router validates audience claim\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtAudience: [\"agentcube-api\"]`\n**WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that has `aud: \"agentcube-api\"`\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate the token successfully\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects token with wrong audience\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtAudience: [\"agentcube-api\"]`\n**WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that has `aud: \"other-api\"`\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 401 Unauthorized with \"invalid audience\" error\n\n### Scenario: Router handles clock skew\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and clock skew tolerance configured\n**WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that expires within the clock skew window\n**THEN** the router SHOULD accept the token as valid\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Metrics\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks JWT validation success\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n**WHEN** a valid JWT is successfully validated\n**THEN** the metric `jwt_validated_total` SHOULD be incremented with label `result=\"success\"`\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks JWT validation failure\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n**WHEN** a JWT validation fails (expired, invalid signature, etc.)\n**THEN** the metric `jwt_validation_errors_total` SHOULD be incremented\n**AND** include error type label\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks JWT token issuance\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n**WHEN** a JWT token is successfully issued\n**THEN** the metric `jwt_issued_total` SHOULD be incremented\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria","oldString":"## Requirement: Key Management\n\n### Scenario: Router loads JWT secret from configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtSecret: \"my-secret-key\"` configured\n**WHEN** JWT validation or issuance occurs\n**THEN** the router SHOULD use \"my-secret-key\" for signing/verification\n\n### Scenario: Router supports RS256 with private key\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and private key configured\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD be signed with RS256 using the private key\n\n### Scenario: Router validates RS256 token with public key\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and public key configured\n**WHEN** a request arrives with RS256-signed JWT\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate using the public key\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/auth.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/workloadmanager/expiration_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":93,"character":15},"end":{"line":93,"character":21}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: metav1"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":51,"character":13},"end":{"line":51,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field IdleTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":52,"character":21},"end":{"line":52,"character":21}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field HealthCheckInterval"},{"range":{"start":{"line":53,"character":20},"end":{"line":53,"character":20}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field HealthCheckTimeout"},{"range":{"start":{"line":54,"character":20},"end":{"line":54,"character":20}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field MaxConnsPerBackend"},{"range":{"start":{"line":57,"character":13},"end":{"line":57,"character":13}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field AuthEnabled"},{"range":{"start":{"line":58,"character":11},"end":{"line":58,"character":11}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/gol