4Z/pkg/router/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/pkg/router/server.go":[]},"diff":"Index: /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md\n===================================================================\n--- /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md\n+++ /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md\n@@ -259,8 +259,11 @@\n - [ ] Public endpoints bypass JWT validation\n - [ ] Token refresh endpoint works correctly\n - [ ] Custom claims can be included in tokens\n - [ ] Invalid credentials are rejected\n+- [ ] Audience claim is validated when configured\n+- [ ] Clock skew is handled gracefully\n+- [ ] JWT metrics are exported (jwt_validated_total, jwt_issued_total, jwt_validation_errors_total)\n \n ---\n \n ## References\n","filediff":{"file":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","before":"# Delta Spec: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing JWT authentication and token issuance in `pkg/router`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-011\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe router module requires JWT-based authentication to secure API endpoints and enable token-based access control. This includes both JWT validation for incoming requests and token issuance for authenticated clients.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Configuration\n\n### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with default configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance is created with `jwtEnabled: true` and no explicit JWT configuration\n**WHEN** the router initializes\n**THEN** it SHOULD use default values: secret from environment or config, algorithm \"HS256\", expiry \"1h\"\n\n### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with custom configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance with JWT configuration: `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"`, `jwtExpiry: \"24h\"`, `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n**WHEN** the router initializes\n**THEN** it SHOULD configure RS256 algorithm, 24 hour expiry, and issuer to \"agentcube\"\n\n### Scenario: Router disables JWT authentication\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance with `jwtEnabled: false` (default)\n**WHEN** HTTP requests are received\n**THEN** the router SHOULD NOT validate JWT tokens\n**AND** no JWT middleware SHOULD be applied\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n\n### Scenario: Router validates valid JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and configured secret\n**WHEN** a request arrives with a valid JWT token in Authorization header \"Bearer <valid-token>\"\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate the token successfully\n**AND** extract the claims into the request context\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects expired JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with an expired JWT token\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 401 Unauthorized with appropriate error message\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects invalid signature JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with a JWT token that has invalid signature\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 401 Unauthorized with \"invalid signature\" error\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects malformed JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with a malformed JWT token (not 3 parts)\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 400 Bad Request with \"malformed token\" error\n\n### Scenario: Router extracts claims from valid JWT\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with valid JWT containing claims: `sub`, `exp`, `roles`\n**THEN** the claims SHOULD be available in request context\n**AND** can be accessed by downstream handlers\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Token Issuance\n\n### Scenario: Router issues JWT token for valid credentials\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint configured\n**WHEN** a POST request arrives with valid username and password\n**THEN** the router SHOULD authenticate the credentials\n**AND** issue a JWT token with user claims\n**AND** return the token in the response\n\n### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured expiry\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtExpiry: \"2h\"`\n**WHEN** a user logs in successfully\n**THEN** the issued token SHOULD have `exp` claim set to current time + 2 hours\n\n### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured issuer\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n**WHEN** a user logs in successfully\n**THEN** the issued token SHOULD have `iss` claim set to \"agentcube\"\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects invalid credentials\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint\n**WHEN** a POST request arrives with invalid username or password\n**THEN** the router SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n**AND** NOT issue a JWT token\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Middleware\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from Authorization header\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with header `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the token\n**AND** validate it\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from query parameter\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware configured to allow query param\n**WHEN** a request arrives with query param `?token=<token>`\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the token from query\n**AND** validate it\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware allows public endpoints\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives at a public endpoint (e.g., `/health`, `/login`)\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD skip JWT validation\n**AND** allow the request through\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware blocks unauthorized access\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives at a protected endpoint without token\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Claims\n\n### Scenario: Router includes user ID in JWT claims\n\n**GIVEN** a user logs in successfully\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD include `sub` claim with user identifier\n\n### Scenario: Router includes roles in JWT claims\n\n**GIVEN** a user with roles \"admin\", \"user\" logs in\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD include `roles` claim with array [\"admin\", \"user\"]\n\n### Scenario: Router includes custom claims in JWT\n\n**GIVEN** a Router configured with custom claims (e.g., `tenant_id`)\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD include the custom claims\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Token Refresh\n\n### Scenario: Router supports token refresh endpoint\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and refresh endpoint configured\n**WHEN** a valid (non-expired) JWT is sent to refresh endpoint\n**THEN** a new JWT token SHOULD be issued\n**AND** the new token SHOULD have fresh expiry time\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects refresh with expired token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT refresh enabled\n**WHEN** an expired JWT is sent to refresh endpoint\n**THEN** the router SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Key Management\n\n### Scenario: Router loads JWT secret from configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtSecret: \"my-secret-key\"` configured\n**WHEN** JWT validation or issuance occurs\n**THEN** the router SHOULD use \"my-secret-key\" for signing/verification\n\n### Scenario: Router supports RS256 with private key\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and private key configured\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD be signed with RS256 using the private key\n\n### Scenario: Router validates RS256 token with public key\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and public key configured\n**WHEN** a request arrives with RS256-signed JWT\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate using the public key\n\n### Scenario: Router validates audience claim\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtAudience: [\"agentcube-api\"]`\n**WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that has `aud: \"agentcube-api\"`\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate the token successfully\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects token with wrong audience\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtAudience: [\"agentcube-api\"]`\n**WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that has `aud: \"other-api\"`\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 401 Unauthorized with \"invalid audience\" error\n\n### Scenario: Router handles clock skew\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and clock skew tolerance configured\n**WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that expires within the clock skew window\n**THEN** the router SHOULD accept the token as valid\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Metrics\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks JWT validation success\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n**WHEN** a valid JWT is successfully validated\n**THEN** the metric `jwt_validated_total` SHOULD be incremented with label `result=\"success\"`\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks JWT validation failure\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n**WHEN** a JWT validation fails (expired, invalid signature, etc.)\n**THEN** the metric `jwt_validation_errors_total` SHOULD be incremented\n**AND** include error type label\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks JWT token issuance\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n**WHEN** a JWT token is successfully issued\n**THEN** the metric `jwt_issued_total` SHOULD be incremented\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] JWT tokens are validated on protected endpoints\n- [ ] Expired tokens are rejected with 401\n- [ ] Invalid signatures are rejected with 401\n- [ ] Valid tokens expose claims in request context\n- [ ] Login endpoint issues JWT tokens\n- [ ] Token expiry is configurable\n- [ ] Token issuer is configurable\n- [ ] JWT algorithm is configurable (HS256, RS256)\n- [ ] Public endpoints bypass JWT validation\n- [ ] Token refresh endpoint works correctly\n- [ ] Custom claims can be included in tokens\n- [ ] Invalid credentials are rejected\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md`\n- Proposal: `proposal.md`","after":"# Delta Spec: AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing JWT authentication and token issuance in `pkg/router`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-011\n- **Module**: `pkg/router`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe router module requires JWT-based authentication to secure API endpoints and enable token-based access control. This includes both JWT validation for incoming requests and token issuance for authenticated clients.\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Configuration\n\n### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with default configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance is created with `jwtEnabled: true` and no explicit JWT configuration\n**WHEN** the router initializes\n**THEN** it SHOULD use default values: secret from environment or config, algorithm \"HS256\", expiry \"1h\"\n\n### Scenario: Router creates JWT handler with custom configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance with JWT configuration: `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"`, `jwtExpiry: \"24h\"`, `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n**WHEN** the router initializes\n**THEN** it SHOULD configure RS256 algorithm, 24 hour expiry, and issuer to \"agentcube\"\n\n### Scenario: Router disables JWT authentication\n\n**GIVEN** a Router instance with `jwtEnabled: false` (default)\n**WHEN** HTTP requests are received\n**THEN** the router SHOULD NOT validate JWT tokens\n**AND** no JWT middleware SHOULD be applied\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n\n### Scenario: Router validates valid JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and configured secret\n**WHEN** a request arrives with a valid JWT token in Authorization header \"Bearer <valid-token>\"\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate the token successfully\n**AND** extract the claims into the request context\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects expired JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with an expired JWT token\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 401 Unauthorized with appropriate error message\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects invalid signature JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with a JWT token that has invalid signature\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 401 Unauthorized with \"invalid signature\" error\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects malformed JWT token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with a malformed JWT token (not 3 parts)\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 400 Bad Request with \"malformed token\" error\n\n### Scenario: Router extracts claims from valid JWT\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with valid JWT containing claims: `sub`, `exp`, `roles`\n**THEN** the claims SHOULD be available in request context\n**AND** can be accessed by downstream handlers\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Token Issuance\n\n### Scenario: Router issues JWT token for valid credentials\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint configured\n**WHEN** a POST request arrives with valid username and password\n**THEN** the router SHOULD authenticate the credentials\n**AND** issue a JWT token with user claims\n**AND** return the token in the response\n\n### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured expiry\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtExpiry: \"2h\"`\n**WHEN** a user logs in successfully\n**THEN** the issued token SHOULD have `exp` claim set to current time + 2 hours\n\n### Scenario: Router issues JWT with configured issuer\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtIssuer: \"agentcube\"`\n**WHEN** a user logs in successfully\n**THEN** the issued token SHOULD have `iss` claim set to \"agentcube\"\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects invalid credentials\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `/login` endpoint\n**WHEN** a POST request arrives with invalid username or password\n**THEN** the router SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n**AND** NOT issue a JWT token\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Middleware\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from Authorization header\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives with header `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the token\n**AND** validate it\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware extracts token from query parameter\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware configured to allow query param\n**WHEN** a request arrives with query param `?token=<token>`\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD extract the token from query\n**AND** validate it\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware allows public endpoints\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives at a public endpoint (e.g., `/health`, `/login`)\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD skip JWT validation\n**AND** allow the request through\n\n### Scenario: JWT middleware blocks unauthorized access\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT middleware enabled\n**WHEN** a request arrives at a protected endpoint without token\n**THEN** the middleware SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Claims\n\n### Scenario: Router includes user ID in JWT claims\n\n**GIVEN** a user logs in successfully\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD include `sub` claim with user identifier\n\n### Scenario: Router includes roles in JWT claims\n\n**GIVEN** a user with roles \"admin\", \"user\" logs in\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD include `roles` claim with array [\"admin\", \"user\"]\n\n### Scenario: Router includes custom claims in JWT\n\n**GIVEN** a Router configured with custom claims (e.g., `tenant_id`)\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD include the custom claims\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Token Refresh\n\n### Scenario: Router supports token refresh endpoint\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and refresh endpoint configured\n**WHEN** a valid (non-expired) JWT is sent to refresh endpoint\n**THEN** a new JWT token SHOULD be issued\n**AND** the new token SHOULD have fresh expiry time\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects refresh with expired token\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT refresh enabled\n**WHEN** an expired JWT is sent to refresh endpoint\n**THEN** the router SHOULD return 401 Unauthorized\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Key Management\n\n### Scenario: Router loads JWT secret from configuration\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtSecret: \"my-secret-key\"` configured\n**WHEN** JWT validation or issuance occurs\n**THEN** the router SHOULD use \"my-secret-key\" for signing/verification\n\n### Scenario: Router supports RS256 with private key\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and private key configured\n**WHEN** JWT token is issued\n**THEN** the token SHOULD be signed with RS256 using the private key\n\n### Scenario: Router validates RS256 token with public key\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with `jwtAlgorithm: \"RS256\"` and public key configured\n**WHEN** a request arrives with RS256-signed JWT\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate using the public key\n\n### Scenario: Router validates audience claim\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtAudience: [\"agentcube-api\"]`\n**WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that has `aud: \"agentcube-api\"`\n**THEN** the router SHOULD validate the token successfully\n\n### Scenario: Router rejects token with wrong audience\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and `jwtAudience: [\"agentcube-api\"]`\n**WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that has `aud: \"other-api\"`\n**THEN** the router SHOULD reject the request\n**AND** return 401 Unauthorized with \"invalid audience\" error\n\n### Scenario: Router handles clock skew\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT enabled and clock skew tolerance configured\n**WHEN** a request arrives with JWT token that expires within the clock skew window\n**THEN** the router SHOULD accept the token as valid\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: JWT Metrics\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks JWT validation success\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n**WHEN** a valid JWT is successfully validated\n**THEN** the metric `jwt_validated_total` SHOULD be incremented with label `result=\"success\"`\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks JWT validation failure\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n**WHEN** a JWT validation fails (expired, invalid signature, etc.)\n**THEN** the metric `jwt_validation_errors_total` SHOULD be incremented\n**AND** include error type label\n\n### Scenario: Router tracks JWT token issuance\n\n**GIVEN** a Router with JWT metrics enabled\n**WHEN** a JWT token is successfully issued\n**THEN** the metric `jwt_issued_total` SHOULD be incremented\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] JWT tokens are validated on protected endpoints\n- [ ] Expired tokens are rejected with 401\n- [ ] Invalid signatures are rejected with 401\n- [ ] Valid tokens expose claims in request context\n- [ ] Login endpoint issues JWT tokens\n- [ ] Token expiry is configurable\n- [ ] Token issuer is configurable\n- [ ] JWT algorithm is configurable (HS256, RS256)\n- [ ] Public endpoints bypass JWT validation\n- [ ] Token refresh endpoint works correctly\n- [ ] Custom claims can be included in tokens\n- [ ] Invalid credentials are rejected\n- [ ] Audience claim is validated when configured\n- [ ] Clock skew is handled gracefully\n- [ ] JWT metrics are exported (jwt_validated_total, jwt_issued_total, jwt_validation_errors_total)\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Delta Spec: `changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md`\n- Proposal: `proposal.md`","additions":3,"deletions":0},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-011/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775849430065,"end":1775849430085}}}}
